                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d308">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-09-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 3, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Adee states that a telegram from viceroy Nanking relative to Woosung bar has
                    been communicated to him by the minister from China. Says a wholly foreign
                    bureau objectionable; invasion sovereignty of China, and stating the foreign
                    ministers say unless Woosung demands complied with they will not agree to
                    increased tariff.</p>
                <p>Mr. Adee states that prompt general settlement should not be interfered with by a
                    local demand of this character, and directs Mr. Rockhill to cable situation
                    briefly.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
